  "firstAcquaintance": "One of the Ghost tribe's grave keepers, primarily responsible for guiding the way. She points out paths for both the living and the dead.",
  "personality": "Always smiling, yet the warmth never reaches her eyes. She passively goes through many tasks without caring about the results.",
  "like": "Bandages, spider silk",
  "familiarData": "Sherry is a guide who wanders the Ghost tribe's territory, a bright lantern in the world of darkness. Both the living and the dead can receive her guidance.\nHowever, she only points the way and does not care about what happens to those she guides afterward. She became a guide simply to do a job, with no enthusiasm for the work itself.\nThough she lacks passion, she never slacks off, completing tasks mechanically. This personality seems related to her life before death, but ghosts usually cannot remember their past, so she herself is not sure.\nBecause Sherry is heavily influenced by habits from her past life, she prefers to maintain a physical form. Materialization consumes a lot of spiritual energy, but Sherry came up with the idea of wrapping her limbs with bandages to maintain their shape, which is why she is always covered in bandages.",
